Class AbstractPreprocessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.uidaho.junicon.grammars.common.AbstractPreprocessor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IPreprocessor
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractParser, JuniconPreprocessor, StatementDetector

    public class AbstractPreprocessor
extends Object
implements IPreprocessor
    AbstractPreprocessor forms the basis for a preprocessor that filters input lines.

      • getParseUnitFromLine

        public ILineContext getParseUnitFromLine(String inputLine,
                                         ILineContext context)
                                  throws ParseException
        Description copied from interface: IPreprocessor
        Gets the next complete parse unit from a single line of preprocessed input. The parse units are derived from the history of partial or incomplete statements observed so far, appended with the input line. The default behavior is to return the original input.

        The preprocessor may add lines back into the input history, for example from include directives.

        Specified by:
        getParseUnitFromLine in interface IPreprocessor
        Returns:
        found statement, or null if no found statements.
        Throws:
        ParseException

      • isPartialStatement

        public boolean isPartialStatement()
        Description copied from interface: IPreprocessor
        Returns true if the input so far to getParseUnitFromLine does not form a complete parseable statement. Complete statements have matching group delimiters "{}" "()" "[]" and are terminated by a semicolon ";".
        Specified by:
        isPartialStatement in interface IPreprocessor
